<plot>This program chronicles the life and career of George Foreman from the perspective of Foreman and his children. From the mean streets of Houston to the top of his grilling empire, we see how "Big George" became the man we see today. As part of ESPN's Black History Month celebration, Foreman's career is celebrated while we get a glimpse of the family man not usually seen publicly.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?459595</url></doc>
